{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":836,"text":"What was the most\ndifficult job you ever did?"},{"time":3882,"text":"Was it working in the sun?"},{"time":5564,"text":"Was it working to provide food\nfor a family or a community?"},{"time":9134,"text":"Was it working days and nights\ntrying to protect lives and property?"},{"time":13661,"text":"Was it working alone"},{"time":14876,"text":"or working on a project\nthat wasn't guaranteed to succeed,"},{"time":18280,"text":"but that might improve\nhuman health or save a life?"},{"time":21667,"text":"Was it working to build something,\ncreate something, make a work of art?"},{"time":26991,"text":"Was it work for which you were never sure"},{"time":29002,"text":"you were fully understood or appreciated?"},{"time":33113,"text":"The people in our communities\nwho do these jobs"},{"time":35393,"text":"deserve our attention, our love\nand our deepest support."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39417,"text":"But people aren't the only ones\nin our communities"},{"time":41884,"text":"who do these difficult jobs."},{"time":44114,"text":"These jobs are also done\nby the plants, the animals"},{"time":46900,"text":"and the ecosystems on our planet,"},{"time":49356,"text":"including the ecosystems I study:\nthe tropical coral reefs."},{"time":53640,"text":"Coral reefs are farmers."},{"time":55626,"text":"They provide food, income\nand food security"},{"time":58860,"text":"for hundreds of millions\nof people around the world."},{"time":61447,"text":"Coral reefs are security guards."},{"time":64181,"text":"The structures that they build\nprotect our shorelines"},{"time":66962,"text":"from storm surge and waves,"},{"time":68843,"text":"and the biological systems\nthat they house filter the water"},{"time":72533,"text":"and make it safer for us to work and play."},{"time":75552,"text":"Coral reefs are chemists."},{"time":78138,"text":"The molecules that we're discovering\non coral reefs are increasingly important"},{"time":81931,"text":"in the search for new antibiotics\nand new cancer drugs."},{"time":85528,"text":"And coral reefs are artists."},{"time":87707,"text":"The structures that they build"},{"time":89226,"text":"are some of the most\nbeautiful things on planet Earth."},{"time":91800,"text":"And this beauty is the foundation\nof the tourism industry"},{"time":94610,"text":"in many countries with few\nor little other natural resources."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99877,"text":"So for all of these reasons,\nall of these ecosystem services,"},{"time":103161,"text":"economists estimate the value\nof the world's coral reefs"},{"time":105870,"text":"in the hundreds of billions\nof dollars per year."},{"time":109271,"text":"And yet despite all that hard work\nbeing done for us"},{"time":112402,"text":"and all that wealth that we gain,"},{"time":114622,"text":"we have done almost everything\nwe possibly could to destroy that."},{"time":119091,"text":"We have taken the fish out of the oceans"},{"time":121068,"text":"and we have added in fertilizer, sewage,"},{"time":123690,"text":"diseases, oil, pollution, sediments."},{"time":127613,"text":"We have trampled the reefs physically\nwith our boats, our fins, our bulldozers,"},{"time":131510,"text":"and we have changed the chemistry\nof the entire sea,"},{"time":134041,"text":"warmed the waters and made storms worse."},{"time":136693,"text":"And these would all be bad on their own,"},{"time":138868,"text":"but these threats magnify each other"},{"time":140650,"text":"and compound one another\nand make each other worse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":143630,"text":"I'll give you an example."},{"time":145047,"text":"Where I live and work, in Curaçao,\na tropical storm went by a few years ago."},{"time":149396,"text":"And on the eastern end of the island,"},{"time":151309,"text":"where the reefs are intact and thriving,"},{"time":153277,"text":"you could barely tell\na tropical storm had passed."},{"time":156260,"text":"But in town, where corals had died\nfrom overfishing, from pollution,"},{"time":161609,"text":"the tropical storm picked up\nthe dead corals"},{"time":163736,"text":"and used them as bludgeons\nto kill the corals that were left."},{"time":167361,"text":"This is a coral that I studied\nduring my PhD --"},{"time":169702,"text":"I got to know it quite well."},{"time":171295,"text":"And after this storm\ntook off half of its tissue,"},{"time":174398,"text":"it became infested with algae,"},{"time":176091,"text":"the algae overgrew the tissue\nand that coral died."},{"time":179416,"text":"This magnification of threats,\nthis compounding of factors"},{"time":183402,"text":"is what Jeremy Jackson describes\nas the \"slippery slope to slime.\""},{"time":188699,"text":"It's hardly even a metaphor\nbecause many of our reefs now"},{"time":192276,"text":"are literally bacteria\nand algae and slime."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196954,"text":"Now, this is the part of the talk"},{"time":198590,"text":"where you may expect me\nto launch into my plea"},{"time":201503,"text":"for us to all save the coral reefs."},{"time":204835,"text":"But I have a confession to make:"},{"time":207744,"text":"that phrase drives me nuts."},{"time":210363,"text":"Whether I see it in a tweet,\nin a news headline"},{"time":214078,"text":"or the glossy pages\nof a conservation brochure,"},{"time":217689,"text":"that phrase bothers me,"},{"time":219536,"text":"because we as conservationists\nhave been sounding the alarms"},{"time":222488,"text":"about the death\nof coral reefs for decades."},{"time":224916,"text":"And yet, almost everyone I meet,\nno matter how educated,"},{"time":229000,"text":"is not sure what a coral is\nor where they come from."},{"time":233489,"text":"How would we get someone to care\nabout the world's coral reefs"},{"time":236838,"text":"when it's an abstract thing\nthey can barely understand?"},{"time":241371,"text":"If they don't understand\nwhat a coral is or where it comes from,"},{"time":244467,"text":"or how funny or interesting\nor beautiful it is,"},{"time":247158,"text":"why would we expect them\nto care about saving them?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":250510,"text":"So let's change that."},{"time":251852,"text":"What is a coral\nand where does it come from?"},{"time":255287,"text":"Corals are born\nin a number of different ways,"},{"time":257479,"text":"but most often by mass spawning:\nall of the individuals of a single species"},{"time":261726,"text":"on one night a year,"},{"time":263086,"text":"releasing all the eggs\nthey've made that year"},{"time":265823,"text":"into the water column,"},{"time":267041,"text":"packaged into bundles with sperm cells."},{"time":269509,"text":"And those bundles go to the surface\nof the ocean and break apart."},{"time":273009,"text":"And hopefully -- hopefully --\nat the surface of the ocean,"},{"time":275779,"text":"they meet the eggs and sperm\nfrom other corals."},{"time":278024,"text":"And that is why you need\nlots of corals on a coral reef --"},{"time":281156,"text":"so that all of their eggs can\nmeet their match at the surface."},{"time":285254,"text":"When they're fertilized, they do\nwhat any other animal egg does:"},{"time":288386,"text":"divides in half again and again and again."},{"time":291059,"text":"Taking these photos\nunder the microscope every year"},{"time":293561,"text":"is one of my favorite and most\nmagical moments of the year."},{"time":296753,"text":"At the end of all this cell division,\nthey turn into a swimming larva --"},{"time":300730,"text":"a little tiny blob of fat\nthe size of a poppy seed,"},{"time":304488,"text":"but with all of the sensory\nsystems that we have."},{"time":307182,"text":"They can sense color and light,\ntextures, chemicals, pH."},{"time":312862,"text":"They can even feel pressure waves;\nthey can hear sound."},{"time":316253,"text":"And they use those talents"},{"time":317571,"text":"to search the bottom of the reef\nfor a place to attach"},{"time":320428,"text":"and live the rest of their lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322051,"text":"So imagine finding a place\nwhere you would live the rest of your life"},{"time":325451,"text":"when you were just two days old."},{"time":327780,"text":"They attach in the place\nthey find most suitable,"},{"time":330571,"text":"they build a skeleton\nunderneath themselves,"},{"time":332674,"text":"they build a mouth and tentacles,"},{"time":334287,"text":"and then they begin the difficult work\nof building the world's coral reefs."},{"time":339124,"text":"One coral polyp will divide itself\nagain and again and again,"},{"time":342993,"text":"leaving a limestone skeleton\nunderneath itself"},{"time":345358,"text":"and growing up toward the sun."},{"time":347906,"text":"Given hundreds of years and many species,"},{"time":350652,"text":"what you get is a massive\nlimestone structure"},{"time":353014,"text":"that can be seen from space in many cases,"},{"time":355550,"text":"covered by a thin skin\nof these hardworking animals."},{"time":359625,"text":"Now, there are only a few hundred species\nof corals on the planet, maybe 1,000."},{"time":364435,"text":"But these systems house millions\nand millions of other species,"},{"time":369193,"text":"and that diversity is what\nstabilizes the systems,"},{"time":371701,"text":"and it's where we're finding\nour new medicines."},{"time":373939,"text":"It's how we find new sources of food."},{"time":377841,"text":"I'm lucky enough to work\non the island of Curaçao,"},{"time":380206,"text":"where we still have reefs\nthat look like this."},{"time":382486,"text":"But, indeed, much of the Caribbean\nand much of our world"},{"time":386821,"text":"is much more like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":388711,"text":"Scientists have studied\nin increasing detail"},{"time":391758,"text":"the loss of the world's coral reefs,"},{"time":393564,"text":"and they have documented\nwith increasing certainty the causes."},{"time":397149,"text":"But in my research, I'm not\ninterested in looking backward."},{"time":400165,"text":"My colleagues and I in Curaçao\nare interested in looking forward"},{"time":403250,"text":"at what might be."},{"time":404631,"text":"And we have the tiniest reason\nto be optimistic."},{"time":408824,"text":"Because even in some of these reefs"},{"time":410625,"text":"that we probably could have\nwritten off long ago,"},{"time":414298,"text":"we sometimes see baby corals\narrive and survive anyway."},{"time":419193,"text":"And we're starting to think\nthat baby corals may have the ability"},{"time":422492,"text":"to adjust to some of the conditions\nthat the adults couldn't."},{"time":426119,"text":"They may be able to adjust"},{"time":428159,"text":"ever so slightly more readily\nto this human planet."},{"time":432890,"text":"So in the research I do\nwith my colleagues in Curaçao,"},{"time":436957,"text":"we try to figure out\nwhat a baby coral needs"},{"time":439494,"text":"in that critical early stage,"},{"time":441042,"text":"what it's looking for"},{"time":442233,"text":"and how we can try to help it\nthrough that process."},{"time":444797,"text":"I'm going to show you three examples\nof the work we've done"},{"time":447662,"text":"to try to answer those questions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":450575,"text":"A few years ago we took a 3D printer\nand we made coral choice surveys --"},{"time":455374,"text":"different colors and different textures,"},{"time":457334,"text":"and we simply asked the coral\nwhere they preferred to settle."},{"time":460228,"text":"And we found that corals,\neven without the biology involved,"},{"time":463237,"text":"still prefer white and pink,\nthe colors of a healthy reef."},{"time":466420,"text":"And they prefer crevices\nand grooves and holes,"},{"time":469579,"text":"where they will be safe\nfrom being trampled"},{"time":471627,"text":"or eaten by a predator."},{"time":473276,"text":"So we can use this knowledge,"},{"time":474756,"text":"we can go back and say\nwe need to restore those factors --"},{"time":477799,"text":"that pink, that white, those crevices,\nthose hard surfaces --"},{"time":481002,"text":"in our conservation projects."},{"time":482769,"text":"We can also use that knowledge"},{"time":484254,"text":"if we're going to put something\nunderwater, like a sea wall or a pier."},{"time":487817,"text":"We can choose to use the materials\nand colors and textures"},{"time":490881,"text":"that might bias the system\nback toward those corals."},{"time":495487,"text":"Now in addition to the surfaces,"},{"time":497488,"text":"we also study the chemical\nand microbial signals"},{"time":500009,"text":"that attract corals to reefs."},{"time":502061,"text":"Starting about six years ago,\nI began culturing bacteria"},{"time":504985,"text":"from surfaces where corals had settled."},{"time":507101,"text":"And I tried those one by one by one,"},{"time":509958,"text":"looking for the bacteria that would\nconvince corals to settle and attach."},{"time":514748,"text":"And we now have many\nbacterial strains in our freezer"},{"time":517922,"text":"that will reliably cause corals"},{"time":519455,"text":"to go through that settlement\nand attachment process."},{"time":522448,"text":"So as we speak,"},{"time":523671,"text":"my colleagues in Curaçao\nare testing those bacteria"},{"time":526115,"text":"to see if they'll help us raise\nmore coral settlers in the lab,"},{"time":529463,"text":"and to see if those coral settlers\nwill survive better"},{"time":532074,"text":"when we put them back underwater."}]},{"cues":[{"time":534304,"text":"Now in addition to these tools,\nwe also try to uncover the mysteries"},{"time":537553,"text":"of species that are under-studied."},{"time":540839,"text":"This is one of my favorite corals,\nand always has been:"},{"time":544152,"text":"dendrogyra cylindrus, the pillar coral."},{"time":547073,"text":"I love it because it makes\nthis ridiculous shape,"},{"time":550004,"text":"because its tentacles\nare fat and look fuzzy"},{"time":553171,"text":"and because it's rare."},{"time":554635,"text":"Finding one of these on a reef is a treat."},{"time":557695,"text":"In fact, it's so rare,"},{"time":558871,"text":"that last year it was listed\nas a threatened species"},{"time":561411,"text":"on the endangered species list."},{"time":563290,"text":"And this was in part because\nin over 30 years of research surveys,"},{"time":566621,"text":"scientists had never found\na baby pillar coral."},{"time":570803,"text":"We weren't even sure\nif they could still reproduce,"},{"time":573241,"text":"or if they were still reproducing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":575760,"text":"So four years ago, we started\nfollowing these at night"},{"time":578453,"text":"and watching to see if we could\nfigure out when they spawn in Curaçao."},{"time":583992,"text":"We got some good tips\nfrom our colleagues in Florida,"},{"time":586704,"text":"who had seen one in 2007, one in 2008,"},{"time":590786,"text":"and eventually we figured out\nwhen they spawn in Curaçao"},{"time":593483,"text":"and we caught it."},{"time":594866,"text":"Here's a female on the left\nwith some eggs in her tissue,"},{"time":597588,"text":"about to release them into the seawater."},{"time":599532,"text":"And here's a male\non the right, releasing sperm."},{"time":602783,"text":"We collected this, we got it\nback to the lab, we got it to fertilize"},{"time":606491,"text":"and we got baby pillar corals\nswimming in our lab."},{"time":610520,"text":"Thanks to the work\nof our scientific aunts and uncles,"},{"time":613084,"text":"and thanks to the 10 years of practice\nwe've had in Curaçao"},{"time":615965,"text":"at raising other coral species,"},{"time":618182,"text":"we got some of those larvae\nto go through the rest of the process"},{"time":622081,"text":"and settle and attach,"},{"time":623757,"text":"and turn into metamorphosed corals."},{"time":626492,"text":"So this is the first pillar coral baby\nthat anyone ever saw."}]},{"cues":[{"time":631786,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":637230,"text":"And I have to say --\nif you think baby pandas are cute,"},{"time":640428,"text":"this is cuter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":641690,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":644236,"text":"So we're starting to figure out\nthe secrets to this process,"},{"time":647384,"text":"the secrets of coral reproduction\nand how we might help them."},{"time":651089,"text":"And this is true all around the world;"},{"time":652961,"text":"scientists are figuring out new ways\nto handle their embryos,"},{"time":655877,"text":"to get them to settle,"},{"time":657059,"text":"maybe even figuring out the methods\nto preserve them at low temperatures,"},{"time":661617,"text":"so that we can preserve\ntheir genetic diversity"},{"time":664757,"text":"and work with them more often."},{"time":666984,"text":"But this is still so low-tech."},{"time":670260,"text":"We are limited by the space on our bench,\nthe number of hands in the lab"},{"time":675299,"text":"and the number of coffees\nwe can drink in any given hour."}]},{"cues":[{"time":680105,"text":"Now, compare that to our other crises"},{"time":682622,"text":"and our other areas\nof concern as a society."},{"time":686265,"text":"We have advanced medical technology,\nwe have defense technology,"},{"time":689941,"text":"we have scientific technology,"},{"time":691562,"text":"we even have advanced technology for art."},{"time":694012,"text":"But our technology\nfor conservation is behind."},{"time":701022,"text":"Think back to the most\ndifficult job you ever did."},{"time":704662,"text":"Many of you would say\nit was being a parent."},{"time":708314,"text":"My mother described being a parent"},{"time":709995,"text":"as something that makes your life\nfar more amazing and far more difficult"},{"time":714230,"text":"than you could've ever possibly imagined."},{"time":716784,"text":"I've been trying to help corals\nbecome parents for over 10 years now."},{"time":721563,"text":"And watching the wonder of life"},{"time":723757,"text":"has certainly filled me with amazement\nto the core of my soul."},{"time":727808,"text":"But I've also seen how difficult\nit is for them to become parents."},{"time":732450,"text":"The pillar corals spawned\nagain two weeks ago,"},{"time":734654,"text":"and we collected their eggs\nand brought them back to the lab."},{"time":737567,"text":"And here you see one embryo dividing,"},{"time":739649,"text":"alongside 14 eggs that didn't fertilize"},{"time":742547,"text":"and will blow up."},{"time":744532,"text":"They'll be infected with bacteria,\nthey will explode"},{"time":747291,"text":"and those bacteria will threaten\nthe life of this one embryo"},{"time":751057,"text":"that has a chance."},{"time":753576,"text":"We don't know if it was our handling\nmethods that went wrong"},{"time":756563,"text":"and we don't know"},{"time":758214,"text":"if it was just this coral on this reef,\nalways suffering from low fertility."},{"time":763582,"text":"Whatever the cause,"},{"time":764911,"text":"we have much more work to do\nbefore we can use baby corals"},{"time":769452,"text":"to grow or fix or, yes,\nmaybe save coral reefs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":775450,"text":"So never mind that they're worth\nhundreds of billions of dollars."},{"time":778545,"text":"Coral reefs are hardworking animals\nand plants and microbes and fungi."},{"time":783996,"text":"They're providing us with art\nand food and medicine."},{"time":788012,"text":"And we almost took out\nan entire generation of corals."},{"time":791975,"text":"But a few made it anyway,\ndespite our best efforts,"},{"time":796040,"text":"and now it's time for us to thank them\nfor the work they did"},{"time":799196,"text":"and give them every chance they have\nto raise the coral reefs of the future,"},{"time":804045,"text":"their coral babies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":805557,"text":"Thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":806776,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}